title: Iran Ballistic Missile Test Not Violation of Nuclear Deal – White House
text: Last week, Iran’s Defense Minister Hossein Dehghan said that the country had test-fired a new surface-to-surface Emad (Pillar) missile. Following the firing, US officials said that the test had likely violated UN Security Council Resolution 1929, prohibiting Iran from undertaking any activity related to ballistic missiles. ...
